Class Utils

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.ubitech.futuretpm.Utils

  • public class Utils
extends java.lang.Object
    The Utils class is containing various methods to make often-needed tasks as HTTP requests. This class includes 56 static final fields {KEY_REQUEST_CHALLENGE, KEY_RP, KEY_RP_ID, KEY_RP_NAME, KEY_RP_ICON, KEY_USER, KEY_USER_NAME, KEY_USER_ID, KEY_USER_ICON, KEY_USER_DISPLAY_NAME, KEY_ALLOW_PUBLIC_KEY_CREDENTIAL, KEY_ALLOW_PUBLIC_KEY_CREDENTIAL_ID, KEY_ALLOW_PUBLIC_KEY_CREDENTIAL_TYPE, KEY_ALLOW_PUBLIC_KEY_CREDENTIAL_TRANSPORTS, KEY_EXCLUDE_PUBLIC_KEY_CREDENTIAL, KEY_EXCLUDE_PUBLIC_KEY_CREDENTIAL_ID, KEY_EXCLUDE_PUBLIC_KEY_CREDENTIAL_TYPE, KEY_PARAMETERS, KEY_PARAMETERS_TYPE, KEY_PARAMETERS_ALG, KEY_TIMEOUT, KEY_ATTACHMENT, KEY_SESSION, KEY_SESSION_ID, KEY_RPID, KEY_CLIENT_DATA_JSON, KEY_ATTESTATION_OBJECT, KEY_AUTHENTICATOR_DATA, KEY_CREDENTIAL_ID, KEY_SIGNATURE, KEY_DATA, KEY_DATA_ID, KEY_DATA_TYPE, KEY_DATA_RAWID, KEY_DATA_EXTENSIONS, KEY_DATA_RESPONSE, KEY_DATA_RESPONSE_USER_HANDLER, KEY_EXTENSIONS, KEY_EXTENSIONS_CABLE_REGISTRATION, KEY_EXTENSIONS_CABLE_REGISTRATION_VERSIONS, KEY_EXTENSIONS_CABLE_REGISTRATION_RP_PUBLIC_KEY, KEY_ORIGIN, KEY_SEAL_INPUT,

      • sendAndRequestResponse

        public static void sendAndRequestResponse(int request,
                                          java.lang.String TAG,
                                          android.content.Context context,
                                          int method,
                                          java.lang.String url,
                                          org.json.JSONObject jsonBody,
                                          org.json.JSONObject jsonHeader,
                                          java.lang.String mBearer,
                                          int nextRequest,
                                          android.app.Activity activity,
                                          VolleyResponse callback,
                                          java.lang.Class intentClass)
                                   throws ExpireSessionException
        This method makes an Http request to login or authenticate/register an authenticator key or seal/unseal a token . Its implementation is in class: Utils. Type is public. The type or member can be called by any object.
        Parameters:
        request - This specify the request to defined different code eg: 0-login,1-challenge, 2-auth,3-register,4-rest_call_seal_token, 5-rest_call_unseal_token
        TAG - Used to identify the source of a log message. It usually identifies the class or activity where the log call occurs.
        context - The context of the Activity that the message dialog will presented
        method - This specifies the type of the request eg:Request.Method.POST
        url - This String param specifies the Request URL
        jsonBody - The body for the request g:Request.Method.POST
        jsonHeader - The header for the request if something more has to be included like tag -2fa- on the rest call request.
        mBearer - The Bearer returned by the HTTP request
        nextRequest - This is a int that specifies if the get challenge request is for authentication -1-, registration -2-, seal token -3-, unseal token -4- or use - -1 - if there is no further request.
        activity - The activity that will present the dialogs.
        callback - A VolleyResponse that will return the response of a get challenge request to the defined activity.
        intentClass - The class that after a successful login the intent will start
        Throws:
        ExpireSessionException
        See Also:
        VolleyResponse, Context, JSONObject, Activity, Utils

      • onActivityResult

        public static void onActivityResult(java.lang.String TAG,
                                    int requestCode,
                                    int resultCode,
                                    android.content.Intent data,
                                    android.content.Context context,
                                    java.lang.String mBearer,
                                    VolleyResponse callback,
                                    android.app.Activity activity,
                                    java.lang.String sealToken)
                             throws ExpireSessionException
        Dispatch incoming result to the correct fragment. Called when an activity you launched exits, giving you the requestCode you started it with, the resultCode it returned, and any additional data from it. The resultCode will be Activity.RESULT_CANCELED if the activity explicitly returned that, didn't return any result, or crashed during its operation.

        You will receive this call immediately before onResume() when your activity is re-starting.

        We have to call this method from out Activity's Override method onActivityResult to receive security key's information and then perform its registration or authentication. Its implementation is in class: Utils. Type is public. The type or member can be called by any object.
        Parameters:
        TAG - Used to identify the source of a log message. It usually identifies the class or activity where the log call occurs.
        requestCode - The integer request code originally supplied to startActivityForResult(), allowing you to identify who this result came from.
        resultCode - The integer result code returned by the child activity through its setResult().
        data - An Intent, which can return result data to the caller (various data can be attached to Intent "extras").
        context - The context of the Activity that the message dialog will presented
        mBearer - The Bearer returned by the HTTP request
        callback - A VolleyResponse that will return the response of a get challenge request to the defined activity.
        activity - The activity that will present the dialogs.
        sealToken - the given token on the seal rest call otherwise insert an empty string
        Throws:
        ExpireSessionException
        See Also:
        VolleyResponse, Context, Utils
